achievements: Escaped slavery and became a leading voice in the abolitionist movement
Published his autobiography, 'Narrative of the Life of Frederick Douglass, an American Slave'
Advisor to President Abraham Lincoln during the Civil War
Twice awarded the Nobel Prize in Chemistry (1958 and 1980)
Developed methods for determining the amino acid sequence of proteins and the nucleotide sequence of DNA
Pioneering work in molecular biology and genetics
